This place was fantastic. Incredibly friendly. The owner came to our table and talked with us. He was really nice and even gave us a free shot. We ordered the banger mash and Irish stew. Both were very delicious and the portions were very large. Did not have enough room for dessert but will be going back for dessert another time. Great atmosphere as well.

Fantastic service and some of the friendliest bar staff I've come across in Waterford and in fact Ireland. As soon as you come in, you are welcomed and made feel like more than a customer. As a local, its a bar to be proud of. Everyone should come here for a pint!

Great place, really friendly staff. Had a great karaoke night there. Although there wasn't that many people there they made us feel very welcome. The atmosphere was brilliant. Would definitely recommend it.
Great food and super friendly staff.Highly recommended.
Always good food, well priced and friendly professional staff

Such a lovely place. Very cosy and comfortable. The staff are so friendly and welcoming. The chef had no issue with adjusting the menu to suit my taste and the food was absolutely superb. I will definitely return next time I am in Waterford and would highly recommend it.
Great local Irish bar, exactly what's on the tin
Nice friendly bar. Good food. Service is good with a homely feel. Christmas trees and decorations all year round add to the character of the place. Well worth a visit for a pint or a bit of grub.
Superb place with a fantastic and friendly host, excellent food and a great selection of drink. The warmth and welcome was superb and very genuine. Highly recommend visiting here

Amazing local pub. Melisa the owner was extremely attentive and welcomed us with a smile and handshake. Dave the bartender poured a proper pint and Cristine the chef made excellent food. After a week of pubs throughout Ireland we found the best one.
Great food, recommended, good and friendly staff, good music on the weekends,
Nice bar, lovely furnished back heard to sit outside and enjoy ciggies, live music on saturdays.
Fabulous food homely atmosphere good friendly staff
Great value for big helpings of tasty food.
Pub but great grub here friendly chat with staff and music here Saturday nights
Excellent food great staff centre of town
The food here is the best both my husband I have eaten in any place in and around Bandon, hugely recommended...not to be passed ...
Oh my god just had lunch here.cant wait to come back.fab fab fab.the taste of the food out standing.had the three courses so nice
One of the best roast beef dinners I have ever had. The sides were unreal and the portion nearly sent me to sleep.
Fine food great atmosphere
Bradys pasta is sooooo good!
They do lovely food there

If you like seventies music this is the place for you. At least that's what the DJ was playing when we were there, lots of Saturday night fever and BeeGees music. The crowd was older probably 50 and up, and everyone seemed to be having a really good time, even those under 30. The beer selection was very good and the place had a very nice ambience
DJ Jerry on the weekends is the man, does tend to get crowded but great crack non the less :)
The two brothers and staff are great in this lively friendly pub.
Great to watch a game. Older crowd. Good staff and always a good athmospher
Great music & service
Best pub in cork, never a dull moment there! DJ is prob the best ive ever seen! What a laugh!!
Lively atmosphere with a nice local vibe.
Good spot to watch the Munster match!
Grand spot to have a pint and a chat with friends
Great 60s/70s/80s music  Weekends very busy. Great atmosphere. Need to be there early to get seat. Even though you won't be sitting for long. You'll be up on your feet dancing.

Gr8 Craic had by all  music on a regular basis, rocking Gerry on at the weekends, he's a famous north side of the city Dj, plays all genres but especially 80's & 90's music, spacious pub with delicious food during the day time also

Had an amazing time in here on Saturday night, great music and amazing cocktails. There was a DJ on and everyone was up dancing. It's a great spot to go on the weekend. I would highly recommend coming here with friends for cocktails.

The brunch menu caters for everyone, smashed avocados, chicken wings, full Irish or the chicken sandwich, which I had, all available. Nice to get 500mls of still or sparkling from the tap at a reasonable price. Overall, a great brunch.

Probably my favourite Pub in Naas. Beautiful interior, friendly and attentative service, gorgeous food and awesome cocktails. It's a good place any time of the day. Grace's has recently added Tacos to the bar bites menu and they are delicious, fresh and very close to Mexican taco's. Kudos to head chef Michal!
Great spot to meet up with friends for some delicious food and some after work drinks.

Our favourite local bar, slick interior, small but perfectly formed bruch, lunch and dinner menus. Perfect for a visit at any time of the day! Super service from the friendly team, give this place a try, you won't regret it!
Staff were helpful and easily approachable food was delish
Nice atmosphere and a great menu! Lasagna was delicious!

Grace's had been one of Naas's most popular pubs for many years. It has a welcoming feel and a warm atmosphere. The pub grub is especially good. Aside from the food it has a very wide range of beers and wines and is sure to cater for all tastes.
Trendy interior, really nice and friendly staff, tasty food. Recommend it.

This pub has a great atmosphere,  both day and night and is well worth a visit. Staff are very friendly and food and selection for lunch is excellent quality. A great spot for evening and night time too. Very mixed and friendly crowd,  great music and one of the best spots in Naas to socialise and be seen in!
Morning brunches on Sunday are amazing been there often for that... Also lovely place for a few drinks at nighttime always buzzy and busy
Amazing decor, staff are very friendly and the food are amazing. Is a mix of restaurant and pub. Well recommend:)
Great for meeting friends & a brilliant sports bar. Food is yummy.

Very tastefully decorated lounge bar with atmospheric lighting. Interesting layout with variety of furniture, sofas, armchairs table types, nooks and crannies. Also bar area at another end and around a corner but part of the one space (not a separate entrance). Struck me as a good place for a date! Nice relaxing atmosphere!
Big portions of food for great value.Food was really tasty. Really friendly staff and quick service.
Nice pub in cork. They have lots of different entartainment on throughout the week.
Good Pints, Good Food, Great Craic. Went in for a pint after a work outing and ended up playing Bingo. Great fun but not for snowflakes.

Lovely vegan options: Vegan burger with Impossible Burger patty and nice vegan cheese (FYH I think?) and a vegan pizza option that I haven't tried but once the cheese is good what could go wrong with pizza?! You can tell they know their vegan product!
Great food and service, good place to watch a match.

Staff was 100% awesome! Our company had a night there with food tonight and when pizza came, I made the joke "where's the gluten free pizza?" (I can't have high quantity of wheat) to which usually staff replies with a nervous laugh and apologizes and tells me they don't have it.... But not Sober Lane! When I made that joke, the dude just turned around and readily asked what pizza I wanted haha he blew my mind lol well done Sober Lane!!
Great fun on Sundays with head or tails for free drink
Quiz is good craic of a Tuesday evening
Host of the best table quiz in Cork. With Pat the amazing DJ and lovely bar staff. This is the place for all your quizzing needs.
Good food, quite big choice of beers. They have a smoking area there covered by canopy with heated seats. Whole week they do different venues for costumers (bingo, dj, quiz, etc.)
Best goujons in town, unbeliable nachos Vast array of craft beers! Cant beat it!
Had a good time with my friends here during "12 pubs of Christmas"
Very good place to drink, eat spicy foods and have fun.
Great night was had with friends in sober lane Tuesdays= quiz night even though we came second last but it's the effort that counts! DJ Patrick Ahern was also hilarious an entertaining

Very fun and lively place! Great music and DJs. Staff is low key but quick and efficient. Overall a pretty young vibe but not exclusively so by any means. A great place to go and dance but also not hard to find seating when needed!!
Lovely staff,very friendly,food is absolutely beautiful!! Highly recommend this bar!!

Lovely spot on they way from the cork airport, sad we were passing this place for so many years and only checked out now. Our must stop place every time from now on ! Delicious carvery served here, good selection of food,drinks, great service, lovely decorated over years with many memorabilia.
Delicious carvery lunch. HUGE portions. The owner and staff are very welcoming and friendly.

Food was awesome, cook to perfection beef and a vast array of vegtables to satiate the deep hunger before we got on a plane from cork.... Good grub, good service ...would return for another feast next time in cork

Food was awesome, cook to perfection beef and a vast array of vegtables to satiate the deep hunger before we got on a plane from cork.... Good grub, good service ...would return for another feast next time in cork

We were in the area & called in for a carvery lunch. Got 2 half portions for the children which were plentiful. The two adult portions were generous. The food was lovely & the restaurant was not busy. Service was from carvery area
Nice 0lace for a pint and a chat. They sometimes do deals like pint and a pizza. Pizza is lovely here btw

Buffet style food. You line up at the serving table and pay as you get through the line. The lunch menu was harty and the corn beef tasted good with the white suace. There isna good selection of beer at the bar and pleasant service. Very much a locals bar as most people knew each other.

If it's a good wholesome meal your after at the right price well then its bull mccabes is the place to go, we went there before we hit the airport and wer full as a bull coming out of it,see what I did there great atmosphere and very friendly staff
Good food, nice staff and close enough to the airport business park to make it a great lunch spot.

What an amazing place with amazing staff! We were lucky enough to have stayed in the Airbnb just above the pub for our honeymoon. We loved that we could go down to such a beautiful pub when ever we needed food or drinks! The food is delicious and the drinks are great! Derek is such a sweet owner and we loved the chats we had with him in his pub. We can't wait to visit again!

The Bull Mc Cabes is a fantastic pub, good food, wide variety of beverages and good music. It is excellent for lunch, especially its chicken curry half and half. Great atmosphere and fabulous service and staff. We have used it for christenings, communions etc and I cannot fault Derek and the staff. Fantastic.
Great Carvery, and selection of beer on tap and whiskey on the shelf! The Staff here are fantastic.
Quaint pub with a very, small used book selection on the upper floor. Would definitely be a normal hangout if I lived in Cork.
Relaxing atmosphere, great staff, great beer. Highly recommended.
Good spot for a quiet pint and a chat. Hasn't changed much in the 20 years that I've been going there, I daresay it didn't change in the 20 years before that either.
Really relaxed and smashing behind the bar.
Great little pub, good beers good whiskey's! Lively crowd.
Great, mellow atmosphere and friendly service. Plus they have 12 O' Clock Mass IPA on tap
Feels like being in a boat, with a fireplace. Really nice spot for a pint
Great beer selections, great old traditional pub visited by the locals. Wonderful food. Try the shepherd's pie. Excellent!!

Want a nice cosy quiet drink in one of Corks historical pubs, then Dan Lowreys is for you. Comfortable seating, good staff and those WINDOWS. Couldn't stop looking at them. A must visit when you are in Cork.
Excellent spot for a pint and traditional grub!
Nice little snug pub. Drop in for a stout or some food at lunch. Or sit by the fire and read a book
Crackin traditional  Pub worth a visit just to see its front window.. The Beamish is perfik aswell

We came to Ireland for a week, but only came to Cork on a day tour. Luckily, we swung into Dan Lowery's for lunch. Fantastic atmosphere, a great pint, and the best shepherd's pie I've ever had. Charming place with warm service. Definitely highly recommended.
Genuinely old school pub. Pints of stout are also pure cream

Very authentic traditional Irish pub - a rare find nowadays. The Beamish (Murphy's) Irish Stout (Corks Stout) on tap is well worth the visit, stain glass windows are also rare to see. The barman told me they came from an old church in Kilkenny/Kerry. So here's a place that's 2 in One like the holy spirit LOL  however I never went to the top shelf.
Good bar. Bit tight when its busy. But its busy because it's a good spot.

Always a great pint and comfort with the fire going, very helpful and pleasant staff. A great list of whiskeys on the menu, It would be great if they done food. I will always call here when in Kinsale.
An Irish Gem. Great atmosphere and staff that really know their trade and love what they do. A trip to Kinsale is incomplete with out a stop here to take in The Folk House.
What a great place and a great atmosphere for all to enjoy. What a great band they made the night. The big swimming mikeys. Highly recommend a must for a great night.
Best music in Kinsale
Great pub always busy and good atmosphere
Great music and brilliant atmosphere.
Great spot in Kinsale. You can some real hidden gems of whiskey here. A must visit
If music, the occasional drunk, good craic, and drinks are what you are after then rock up here and check out the vibe. It's always an interesting mix.
Excellent pub very friendly and well run. Best beer in kinsale.

The best pub in Kinsale!!! We visit regularly from the US and this place is always great (especially during the "off season"). Locals flock here and the bar staff is amazing! They have a great beer and amazing whiskey selection. The live music is fun and it's always lively on the weekends. Must visit!!
Long established in the very heart of Kinsale this is a busy pub with good live music during the season. Night club next door for those with stamina.

Arthur Mayne's Pharmacy is a great location.  They have a good selection of Irish whiskies. They serve brunch and dinner. The meals are of good value. There is plenty of seating available. It is wheelchair accessible and friendly. However,  when it gets busy it becomes difficult to manoeuvre around. There is wheelchair accessible parking nearby.

This is one of my favourite places for lunch when I'm in centre of Cork. It's an old pharmacy converted to a pub / restaurant. All the old parts of the pharmacy exist, I'm not sure the walls have been redecorated in the last 100 years, shelves. On entering there is the bar and tiny kitchen area, then an old security area like a jail, which now has seating, then a larger seating area which has a safe on the wall, or doors for it. Shelves full of old photography stuff, the days before digital. Saying it hasnt been redecorated sounds dirty but it isn't, lighting is dull but atmospheric, well worth a visit. If you stay to eat, menu is reasonably priced. I always eat the beef or the coronation chicken sandwiches, ( allergies limit my choices) but friends have enjoyed other dishes. Staff are always friendly. Some local brews available but as I'm usually driving I tend to stick to mint tea.
Just brilliant. Make this a stop on your your night out. Old pharmacy now serves drinks and food. I thoroughly enjoyed it here. Small but a cracking atmosphere.
Great choice in wines and a very hipster place for drinks. When central you try to find value for money and with the over all experience I felt it was mid range prices with good experience
What a unique place. Original pharmacy books from 1930's at least. All kinds of products from the past.

This place was really cool. It was an old pharmacy turned into a bar. It had all the old pill and glass bottles all over the walls. And on the top floor they had a cocktail bar, where I ordered a old fashion, excellent!
A great spot to have amazing tapas and a few drinks. Food is incredible, prawns and goats cheese being my favorite. Cosy and great atmosphere especially for dates. Well worth a visit.
Lovely porter and tapas in a remarkable interior with inner Street at the back of stunning atmosphere - must try once you are in Cork!
Nice cocktail bar hidden above the main bar. Great views of the street below from the large windows. the old style decor adds to the feel of the place. Cocktails arent bad either.
Incredibly friendly and helpful staff, cozy location above the old apothecary, and most important of all, a fantastic collection of delicious custom cocktails at the full service bar.

FAB-U-LOUS. Top notch tapas style food served with panache and by extra friendly staff in this former pharmacy (or 'de chemist' ) Excellent whiskey selection in the bar upstairs. An absolute MUST VISIT
Very cool place. Comfortable and warm. Feels like sitting in someone's living room
One of my favourite bars in Cork City! Lovely cosy atmosphere and gorgeous food! Try their halloumi fries! Absolutely delicious! Staff are always friendly also!

This place is a gem in the heart of Cork to enjoy some nice wine and relax after a long day. I often go there with my partner. Also, recently, I organized an event at Meade's for about 15 people. The staff were very understanding, friendly, and helpful. People I invited loved the place, I am sure they gained a few regular customers that night! Thanks for all the understanding!
Good selection of wines, lovely atmosphere. Great service.
Friendly staff and nice atmosphere. They had a decently large selection of wine as well.
Great meeting room. Bar just downstairs for refreshment. Friendly staff.
Lovely quiet spot in the centre of town.
Excellent service, lovely staff
lovely little wine bar in cork city, can't recommend enough, the staff are very nice and the atmosphere is great, lovely wine with no beer on tap, this wine bar is sophisticated and fun, great spot
Unassuming exterior hides a charming, Victorian era interior that is now home to a cosy wine bar. Great selection of wines and simple tapas. A calm oasis in the heart of the city.
Nice and relaxed bar. Great place for a romantic drink or even to just catch up with friends and chat.
Quiet and very cozy. Bon fire and great wine selection
Cork's best kept secret

One of the best spots for nightlife and a good diverse crowd. Ive never seen a fight here which is something! The pizza from the bus is good too. I heard rumours that they are going to close this place down to build a hotel. That would be another major blow to Dublins nightlife scene. I often run into Americans there who think the place is very unique and a great pub. Heres hoping the Bernard Shaw remains open for many more years.

Well it's not "all spent" but I had great time that evening with a surprisingly great pizzaaaa in back yard.... I mean the place is full of stickers which made me laugh and enjoy them a lot... well back to pizza which made my day there... I wanted spicy and I f...g got it... thanks a lot!!! will be there again...

Very cool drinking and smoking area out back in the open air. Full of graffiti which adds to the atmosphere. There's a unique pizza place inside the double decker bus as well. Recommended during a nice day out.

This is one of my favorites pubs in Dublin, the atmosphere of the place is unique. Moreover, there is a pizza place inside the double decker bus and it's amazing, their options for flavour is great you can find from vegan to meat lovers. Recommended!
Historical pub, nice staff, well located nearby Harcourt luas station and plenty of local buses and taxis. They have pizza in they backyard. On weekends it is really busy.

Love the place! An amazing place for a hangout with firends and they serve one of the amazing pizzas! Theres a bus inside, which actually serves the pizza. On weekends it will be very crowded, so very difficult to find a seat. Mostly its frequented by very young crowd and college students. It can be too loud so wont recommend as a hangout with your date, specially if you are meeting for the first time. Weekdays are quiet, so maybe that will be a good time. The ambience is good with some old pub like tables and some funky designs.

Great selection of beers, can be a very busy spot but there is a great outdoor smoking area. The pizza from the bus is amazing too. A good crowd inside here, can sometimes be pretentious. Worth a visit even just for the "Eatyard" set up out the back.

One of the pubs with strongest personality in Dublin. Very laid back, hippie if you wish, with awesome perks like the eatyard and a pizza double decker bus. It's one of the very few places in Ireland with a proper beer garden.
Really good beer selection. Amazing court yard with hipster truck food.

This place is really cool and has pretty much everything you could possibly want - a pub, a massive outdoor area, a pizza bus! The front facade is very charming and looks like a small pub, but it hides a substantial interior, with so many different places to sit, you can have whatever sort of night you want (date, group, dinner or after-work drinks). I would highly recommend the pizza bus.

Are you tired of Instagram pubs and want to meet real people, have a nice conversation, choose from variety of food and listen to not mainstream music? This pub is for you! Don't expect luxury, expect good grunge type of good time!

Lovely pub & music venue located near the canal. Great drink selection, with ample seating both inside and out. Outdoor area has a great pizza place housed in an old blue bus, so that's pretty whopper! Also in the outdoor area is "Eatyard", an open-air food market with some of Dublins best independent food & drink on offer every Thursday to Sunday. Must-visit for tourists and locals alike.
My favourite place to go for a nice drink with friends. The atmosphere in the beer garden is amazing, the staff are great and the pizza from the bus is the best, most fresh pizza I've ever had.

We visited the White Rabbit for a whiskey tasting and haven't been there before. The staff was amazing from start to finish. We've been treated with a mixed platter of smoked wings, ribs, brisket sliders and corn on the cob followed by a lovely dessert which I forgot what it was because of the meat sweats but i think it was a whiskey bread pudding. All was absolutely delicious. Wine, beer and of course the whiskeys have also been top class. The selection of whiskeys from all over the world is top. We'll be back for more soon.
Really nice, friendly pub. Good vibe and the food was outstanding plus good range of drinks. Would definitely visit again

This was a great surprise; all our food was delicious. Pulled pork baps, brisket, corn bread, pancakes all excellent. The service was brilliant, really genuine & friendly. They have a huge craft beer list (which I'm regretting I tried so many (!!)). One of our group was veggie & she was totally catered for. I'll definitely be back again
Great place to try local beers that aren't Guiness. In house BBQ was a great change of pace. They sat us immediately, very friendly and helped us find what our taste was.
The white rabbit is a very nice Irish pub with yummy pulled pork and a variety of beer and whiskey. Super friendly staff. Thanks again for a perfect evening.
Thoroughly enjoyed our dinner in the white rabbit. The beef brisket was amazing. Staff were so polite and helpful
Beyond delicious. The chef really knows what he is doing! Great atmosphere and beer selection. Loved it, we are coming back soon
Good barbecue thought the sides leave room to be desired. The brisket is usually on point and nice selection of whiskeys too.
This place always delivers. The food and the staff, the staff and the food. Not sure which id put first both 100%. Then the music is second to none. Thanks so much for last night.
Cosy restaurant-bar with great selection of beers and tasty dishes. Nice if you can share them with friends. the pork-belly cubes are amazing !

Do NOT leave Cork without visiting the White Rabbit. This is the best bbq around, and their selection of beer coupled with positive vibes and humor make this place worthy of a pilgrimage of the palete!
A great variety of delicious food and friendly staff! Very filling and well priced. Local brewed beer on tap is a must.
Best place in the city to go for smoked meats, bourbon and craft beers and the the staff are super nice
Haven't had the chance to try alot of the menu but their pancakes (best I've ever had by the way) and amazing service makes me want to go back as soon as I can!! Hidden gem in the city

Quirky little bar...downstairs for beers and wines etc and through a door to another quirky bar upstairs for cocktails.'Old Fashoned' cocktails were amazing! Go through the bar to a courtyard outside. Very pretty.

The band that played that night were crazy awesome. I think they were called Henge. The bar's selection of craft beer and whiskey was unbelievable so I would highly recommend. Also they have a restaurant and the aroma was heavenly
Great place. Pubs share the lane, you can buy a pint in one and walk into the next pub with it. Different music playing in each pub also!
An entertaining night out with a wide variety of beverages at reasonable prices with a good selection of live music scene in Cork. A must visit if you are in the vicinity of Cork City.
Really nice pub. Love the ambiance. The bartenders are always nice. I should come back here for one their famous dance lessons or music show
Great atmosphere and goid variety of music for all tastes and a big venue

This place is epic! Different events going on every night of the week from swing dancing classes to drag shows, there is something for everyone. There is 3 different rooms with 3 different ambiances to choose from as well as a heated outdoor area for smoking and mingling. People seem to be interested in meeting new people and just having a chat here, more than other spots.
Always great nights here! The gigs are always good, the music is always good, and there's always great craic!

Great pub in the city center. They have a great bar and lounge as well as a late bar with Djs and bands. There is a large heated area in the entrance lane for smokers. Staff are friendly service is fast. They have plenty of good bands on and it's a good venue for gigs. Definitely well worth a visit if you like a lively night out.
Great spot for live music,make sure you get in early if you want a seat. Bouncers are a great bunch of lads
Very good variety from bar to disco to live music
Always great live bands (mostly kinda ska, rock, blues, jazz), nice for a bit if dancing, specially if you're not a pro (like me!). Never crowded, always good vibes. Great selection of craft beers.
Beautiful pubs and outdoor seating area. Nice during the week to have a quiet chat and glass of wine

Fantastic venue, truly unique! You are greeted by a long alleyway somewhat representative of and old style Street! There are three main bars and all the staff are very friendly! Great selection of drinks and if you venture to the fourth bar, Arthur Maynes, you can get beautiful tapas served until 1am! Would wholeheartedly recommend this to anyone!
Lovely cosy pub. Open fire. Old world charm. Great service. Warm welcome. Excellent music. Friendly customers. Succulent Smithwicks, Guinness & Wines etc. Safe location.
Great point and great music atmosphere brilliant.

We left Siamsa Theatre in Tralee tonight after the Eddi Reader show which was fantastic and shot up to BETTY,S BAR where we were welcomed by the host's in time for a pint/short a welcome nightcap. Recommended.
Fabulous atmosphere and traditional music
Great pup great Guinness and great atmosphere
Everyone here is lovely! We had a splendid time and enjoyed every moment.
Traditional Irish bar located in an ideal location within tralee town. Traditional Irish music played every Saturday. Lovely staff and great beer
Great Craic,and a handsome pint of porter
Great music & pints, lovely staff; friendly atmosphere, spotless facilities, all good
Nice laid-back vibe, and a truly fabulous pint of Guinness. I'll be back...
Excellent place to visit, friendly staff and cosy atmosphere. Will go back again
Good pint... Local clientele.... Good fun... Great staff... Good honest local pub with the best pint of Guinness in Tralee :)
Authentically friendly. Dennis was patient with my questions and poured a perfect pint of Beamis. Donald provided great insight on where to go, how to get there and what to see out west.
Amazing pub. No tables. Just benches on either side of the room and great pints.
Serious G. Get the snug
One of my favourite pubs in Cork.
One of the best pints of Guinness in Cork City.
Cosy, warm and genuine pub. One of the nicest in Cork city.
Great little old pub. Lovely atmosphere Cash only. A must for drink.
Traditional Irish pub in the heart of Cork City. Worth a visit if you want taste of real old fashioned Irish pub!
A home away from home. One of my favourite haunts for a pint of Murphy's. Mary the owner is always welcoming and is very popular with locals in Cork city.
A grand old place. Worth a visit
One of the last authentic old Irish pubs left in the city. The pints are pure cream to top that off.
No trip to Cork should be without a trip to this place for a Beamish!!!!!!!
A taste of old ireland in the middle of cork city!
Proper 'old man pub'. Great little spot and the couple who own and run it are so friendly and accommodating.

Nice place to watch sports, i would advise to book in advance if you want sits for a big group. Nice garden and smoking area. I had nachos and the waitress was kind enough to understand my food preferences and separate all the sauces for me.
Good vibes, good drinks, good food. Will definitely come back. They stream all sorts of live games so make sure check this place out!
Good place for drinks on a Friday night busy but not that metal so doesn't take long to get served at the bar. Great big space also and you have a choice of different areas and bars.
Nice big place. Good music. Has a dance club feel.

Really good bar to have a drink with someone and also dance but generally packed and no tables the more later it gets especially on the weekend. The smoking area is like a sunbed so if you want to cool down you need to go outside the living room.
A great place in middle of the city. Have big screens to watch sports. Good for a bigger group, to sit in the open or closed area. Pizza at this place is simple but great taste.

A nice well managed place. A lot of dashboard screens that enables you watch your preferred games/matches. Entrance is totally free as there are securities and the door to check for under age group. It has a separate section for smokers and a mini section for fast food restaurant.
Nice place. Big screen and good ambience. Big smoking place in the backside.
Not only sports lovers will enjoy this bar for great big screens inside and easy watch any of good match... Great atmosphere with good selection of drink and food. So go and try :)
Even if I don't drink I had to follow my friends to this nice place, the staff is amazing and the environment is just perfect

Plenty of TV screens on the walls to watch sports etc. Drinks selection are pretty good. A bit too loud for my liking but the back area connects to 4 other pubs(common area) and you can get a bit of quiet out there.
I love to spend my spare time here on drinks n watch matches on big screen ,
Nice place to relax with friends. Great beer.
Wow. It's great place in Dublin 1 to enjoy your evening with friends/colleagues. Four different pubs inside-out.
A good place to share with friends, large terrace and good atmosphere
Lovely food and excellent wait staff. The warm chicken salad is especially nice
Great bar has been the best bar in Douglas for years. Good pints, atmosphere and food.
Great atmosphere, I had the burger and it was the best burger I have ever had, the staff are very friendly and couldn't do enough for us. Highly recommend
Very friendly workers, kids loved it and food was fab! Well worth a visit.

We had 25 sitting for food for my sons conformation and all I can do is praise them . The food was delicious and the staff were all fabulous especially Sarah it was so relaxed and nothing was any trouble. I would highly recommend ye.
As always staff very friendly and helpful. Food very good pints excellent.

Traditional (large) Pub with astone floor and great feel. Was at a trade session on a Tuesday night, fire and all. was driving so stuck to the alcohol free beers and am pleased to say they had a nice selection of 3.
Excellent authentic Irish fare, great service, parking out back, 10/10.
It's a grand pub. Quite big but with a bunch of snugs and quiet corners
a great venue for Irish music and the staff are fantastic
Really nice bar, friendly staff, nice beer garden smoking area

We celebrated our 2nd child's christening in The South County recently after also doing the same for our first child. From start to finish both events were fantastic. Tom and his staff really looked after us and nothing was too much trouble. The food was excellent and plentiful and all our guest stayed long into the night enjoying the crack in the bar. I couldn't recommend the bar, it's staff & management highly enough.
Celebrated my 60th here. Good food and friendly staff.
Friendly pub and super grub kept all the Redmond's happy thank you very much
The food was great, everyone at my table had a different dish and will enjoyed it
You can't beat Dan's bar in ireland great service, great people and lovely place.
Had a great night for game nite. They put on snacks for us and service at the bar was great.
Amazing old fashioned service. Food great, a popular place with locals.
Great atmosphere, good food and lovely staff
Great service Lovely staff. Watched rugby game Munster v Saracens
Drink good, staff excellent and cutomers friendly. Warm cosy pub for a drink.
This place is great and the smoking area is extremely comfortable to sit out in! Nice and friendly bar staff too
What a lovely little friendly pub that my hubby came across while on holiday we had a dinner in here the food was lovely and the price was reasonable the staff were lovely and couldnt do enough
Great lunchtime food and service. Good atmosphere for drinks in the evening
Great service, very helpful and friendly staff, food was on the table super fast at 1230pm, delicious and very filling! very handy parking both out front and just down the road
Great place!! Nice atmosphere great staff and the prices are reasonable. Well done to all at the Old Oak.

First time I've been there. Went to the bar and didn't know what to drink. Asked them if they could recommend me anything and just ordered whatever they told me to. By far my best decision and my most favorite beer until now. Really nice atmosphere and there is also live music
Lovely pub, always shows sporting events and is hopping with diverse young and old people on the weekend's

It is great for watching all Sports screens everywhere. A well equipped bar plenty of seating and very spacious. St. Patrick's Day the music and Craig was great after of course we watched Liverpool win  Also they are the cheapest on there street for a Pint of Bulmers. Staff always so accommodating especially with children.
Big pub with a dancefloor and good prices. The people were pretty young in here.
Really great for a night out, good music and dance area, good staff
Magical bar with its in-house concert venue.

What an enormous bar ....very friendly staff. Even got to see a Spanish League game. Well worth a visit. Though on Sundays there isn't any food. But don't worry just pop into the Oliver Plunkett, which is right opposite, and you will leave with a nice full belly.
I like it here because there are always lots of people, good music and you can drink and enjoy with friends.
One of the oldest in cork city near to oliver plunkett. Good live music..enough space to dance..best place to satisfy your thirst
Very lively and well run good craic good music played plenty of 80s tunes a very enjoyable experience
A good place to watch the Irish Rugby match.The sound was turned on. Good quality drink and friendly staff.
Great atmosphere on a sat afternoon.. lots people coming and going. Lovely range of tasty beers. Outside seating area perfect.. didn't eat but the pizzas that were being served up looked delicious

A nice bar set back from the road down an alley. Inside is a cosy bar area, and out back a covered terrace where you can get good pizza from Pompeii Pizza. Beer n pizza, seriously who could ask for more? Both the red and the IPA are excellent beers. Well worth considering for a chilled evening out.

Knowledgeable bar staff. Mostly Franciscan well beers which is very extensive. Excellent whiskey selection. Need to find a place to crash in Cork to sample their wares. Non-alcoholic beverage range good too for all the drivers. Pizzas supplied by Pompeii pizzas excellent. Will return.

Loyal customer here. Ive been coming and going for the past 6 years. Great staff. The beer garden is great and most of it is heated and sheltered. Outdoor fire. Pizza place serves great pizza at reasonable prices. Loved the old 2 for a 5 drink vouchers when I was a student. Their own beer is brewed on the property and they have a very wide selection to offer. If you are ever out and not drinking they also serve very nice coffee. Something for everyone

Lovely beer garden! When we went there was live music and many flowers in bloom. Our group split a flight of their beers to see which ones we liked best. We ended up getting glasses of the stout and wheat beers.

What an amazing pub and beer garden. Plenty of places to sit and an excellent drink selection. I had the Mango Strawberry Cider and hubby had the Rebel Red. We had dinner plans already but the pizza was extremely tempting!
Loved the food the drinks and pretty much everything about this beer garden. It is very lively with traditional live music. Nice atmosphere all around

Old school pub with its own beers. Try the Shandon Stout and you might forget about the others. Friendly add helpful staff despite our obvious tourist naivety. You'll need to order at the bar. They've also partnered with a fabulous Italian pizza joint in the beer garden.

Fantastic little bar and brewery all the beer they produce is excellent the stout is fantastic best I've had in Ireland. The out door area with wood fired pizza kitchen and live music was the highlight of my trip to Cork City.

Simply one of the best pubs in Cork. Serves great craft beer brewed in site. Has interesting guest draughts so there's always something new. The beer garden is the place to be on a sunny evening in Cork. Has a cocktail bar upstairs and a pizza place in the back. Literally has it all. Top notch

A cool place. I guess it's one of Cork's landmarks. A must visit place. A nice Irish pub where you can sit get some work done, read a book or even have a loud conversation with friends. Their house brewed stout bear maybe the smoothest I've tasted.

We did the beer tour and Claudia was fantastic. The beer was excellent. The inside had aperfect pub atmosphere and the patio was spacious, well shaded, and clean. Staff was friendly. Would definitely recommend visiting!
Amazing cocktails to be had here. Barmen are always a friendly lot here to when i visit and happy to chat if the place isn't too busy. The bar as it is decorated and furnished is oozing in character!

Great place to spend some time with friends and partner. Cocktails are something different and absolutely recommendable. Staff is very nice and always up for help especially in regards to picking the right cocktail. DANDELION Cocktail is one of my favourites. Will come back!

What an enjoyable evening! Expect to pay a bit more for high quality but it is worth it! Kieran was an exceptional bartender who was super accommodating with drink requests and chit chat! Great atmosphere and overall a really enjoyable time!

Fantastic ambience, amazing cocktails, spectacular staff, this must easily be the best cocktail bar in Ireland. The staff really know their stuff, the drinks are marvellous, the food is remarkably good. This place is the full package and then some, very well worth revisiting because they change their menu and replace award-winning cocktails for cocktails that are surely going to win awards.
Great food, beer and atmosphere, plus stuffed ferrets. Worth a visit just to look at the cocktail menu.

Great cocktails on a menu that changes regularly. Staff are also willing to make any other cocktail for you provided that they have the ingredients! Service is very good and the bar itself is very calm and quaint.
Third time here.. Still such a lovely place to go whether it's with the girls or on a date! Can't recommend it highly enough
Fantastic cocktails, and a cheese board to die for.
A very well designed bar with a great selection of drinks. A great place to go for a glamourous night out with lively cocktails and wine on offer. The courtyard is a nice outdoor feature.

Really friendly staff, nice ambiance and decor. The food was the tastiest I've had in a while. Definitely have the breads with the tapenade, sun-dried tomato and pesto. Was surprisingly the highlight of the food. The pizza was delicious as well as the chicken wings. Will be back.
Good cocktails good food good atmosphere. Definitely the place to go if you are in cork.
Great place with fantastic staff who know exactly what they're doing. Cask was a great experience for a party.
Best Cocktails you'll get... Will hold itself against wherever it is you think you drank your best cocktail before... And most likely beat it.
Nice pub for a pint. Friendly staff and nice relaxed atmosphere. Plenty beers to choose from on draught which is great.
Great bar. Great atmosphere for sports. Management & staff are very friendly and helpful. Brunch/Lunch menu served till 2:30pm is fabulous & very reasonably priced.
Cissie youngs is a realy nice place to go and relax for a drink and watch the latest match that's on are just to meet friends for a drink and the and tom and he's son's are very nice people.
Great atmosphere. Lovely pub for a drink, meeting friends, watching sports or a quick lunch. Live music thurs nights
Good sports pub with friendly staff. The pizza that is there recently is very good.
Great spot, a true local gem.
Grt Location, grt Athmosphere & Music grt nite @ Engagement party
Great stop for the match. Good selection of craft beers on draught too
If you're looking for a quiet pint with a good atmosphere, Cissie's is the spot
Great food, great staff, perfect bar to watch Rugby, GAA & Football comfortably, with an excellent selection of craft beers.
Had some nice drinks here over Christmas, had an enjoyable music session going on down the back
Serves food from 11am to 3pm monday to Friday also shows sports and live music at the weekends also caters for party's.
Really good place. The atmosphere was nice did the pub quiz and also eat before. Reasonably priced food (get what you pay for) not bad. Would recommend to families etc.
Food lovely a really good variety of choice on the menu, and cheap prices. We went as a large group of about 30 and they accommodated for us in a space together. Staff were friendly and helpful.

Excellent service courtney really impressed me and believe she will go far. Her customer servoce skills and management was impressive. She also helped other staff good team worker. She made our day also the food was excellent. Enjoyable experience will be returning

Went from work for a colleague's birthday and was very impressed with the whole place. It is nice and airy, lots of little alcove spaces if you want to be out of the way. The menu is huge! Loads of choice, with specials on certain days. Very kid friendly too. Food is excellent, you get your monies worth. I'd definitely recommend a visit.
Nice atmosphere and not too busy might be busier in the evening. Delicious food well priced and with a good selection and an equally good selection  of drinks. Clean and tidy with friendly staff.
Lovely place, food was excellent and atmosphere great. Will definitely go again
Probably one of the best in my favourite chain... From the food, drink, and service to the decor.... Top notch
Nice place to go to. The food is very tasty and the service is very good. The staff are extremely friendly and helpful.
Polite Vicar is a very nice pub. Centrally located. Plenty of parking. Food is very good quality. Relaxed atmosphere.
Great place for a night out. Ordinary food and good hygiene. As well an option to watch live most of the Champions league and Premier legue games
Lovely place to eat and nice atmosphere! The food is great and you must try the Starks as they come out sizzling
Lovely welcoming place looks really nice now it's been done up. Staff are nice food is lovely a really nice place to eat
Food is excellent value for money. Gets busy so might be good idea to book if more than two of you.
Very nice pub great food will recommend to friends and family
Pensioners menu is brilliant value for money, and the food was fabulous .

My wife and I have been to Limerick to visit some friends last weekend and they took us to the Flannerys after dinner. We had an amazing time. Such a great team.! Very well trained Id say. Very busy night for them and it seemed they were having the time of their life. I had the chance to talk to one of them and this guy was very helpful and funny too. The venue looked great and its such big space. Lots of people in but didnt feel overcrowded. If you are looking for a fun night, dont miss it. Visit this place. Well be back to Ireland in August probably, so Ill see you soon Flannerys.
Nice place,friendly staff. Cocktails amazing
Had a party there last night with a group of friends in the front bar. Really catered for brilliantly by lovely staff and the place just has a great atmosphere.
Great bar with an amazing atmosphere! Great service and staff.
The refurbishments are fab. Lovely atmosphere and a great variety of drinks including cocktails.
Held a 40th birthday party there last night .brilliant staff were so accommodating and we had a ball
Great spot, if you're out for a quiet drink or a in a party mood. It's big enough to accommodate both.
During weekend good place for a big party! Staff perfect
A mecca in Limerick for anything rugby related. Big size pub with good beers and friendly staff.
On a trip to Ireland and went to flannerys in limmerik for a drink. Best local pub to go see. Wonderful people and bartender. Made us feel at home. Made our whole trip. Thank you so much.
This is a great, pub, you can gave a quiet drink in one of tge bars or have a party night in the other, lovely balcony area, and nice outdoor section. Can highly recommend it

This place is a fun place to chill and relax. They have a wide selection of beer and whiskey.  The music and ambience are well suited for this place. The servers are easy to chat with. They do their best make you feel at home and welcomed. The layout is simple and easy to navigate. There are benches for groups or stools for small groups.
An authentic centuries old pub serving a great selection of beer on tap, traditional Irish music and a fantastic historical comedy dinner show upstairs a few nights a week. Love this place!

I loved the ambience here... Nice place to go with friends who loves Irish music... I just fell in love with the group of people who sang and played different instruments with harmony...  Very pleasant staff.. varieties of beer.. altogether had a great time in this pub...
Great spot, great trad music, service was very good too- the place has character

Wow what a place full to the celling with Character. Old style Irish traditional pub. Full selection of beers and guest ales and beers. Fabulous friendly staff go above and beyond there service. Brilliant place for live music. Snugs here for private drinking. My favourite bar.
The best place for a private party up stairs fuction room and great staff.

I was just at this pub tonight. The live Irish folk music has inspired me to listen to more when I go back to Canada. Very talented musicians. The staff are pleasant. I wish I tried the food, but I will next time I return. Even if youre a tourist, it makes you feel like you arent. I highly recommend coming here.
Amazing place for a pint and listen to a good irish music
At the Sunday night Singer's Club for the first time in ages, wonderful singing, new friends, old friends, and a great pint of Murphy's.
Interesting old pub on an old street in Cork city.. Lots of artifacts on walls...old photos of interest to locals and visitors. Friendly staff. Food also served.

We stopped by early and were told they didn't serve food, but they recommended The Flying Enterprise. we returned after dinner and spent a delightful night listening to the Cork Singing Club sing traditional folk songs as well as their own compositions. This neighborhood bar was just the fit for a Sunday night.
Cosy classic Irish bar, good priced beamish, very nice staff, great service. One downfall is cash only bar so do come prepared :)
A great place to spend the evening if you can get by the fireplace!
This is a good venue for quizzes and events that are different. It's a real Irish pub
Typical old Irish pub with lots of seating and character! Function room upstairs with a stage where plays/ events are held. Finger food available for events

Really wholesome pub food. Big portions and a great price. Staff are super nice and helpful. Lots of clean comfortable seating and good parking. Book your table at the weekend to avoid disappointment as it can be quite busy.
Love this place good food great pints nice and clean. Very spacious

The Arches is by far and away the most underrated bar in Mallow. If you were to take this bar and put it in Cork City, it would be packed constantly. Amazing food, reasonable prices, a smoking area that covered and heated, has a pool table and a free jukebox.
Burgers are great! plenty of parking and very friendly staff! keep it up!
Great food fabulous staf always a warm welcome
Had a lovely meal last night with our visiting friends from Australia. Staff were very friendly and the food was fab.
Excellent service, fantastic food! Nice and friendly staff.
Local pub conveniently located opposite the Church. Enjoyed coffee, soup and local friendly service.

We arrived for lunch one Sunday, everyone starving. The carvery was right inside the bar doors. Food steaming hot  . Put loads on your plate, regardless of what you ordered. Paying was easy, no hold ups or queues even though the place was busy. Great food. Great friendly staff. And needless to say we were well stuffed leaving. Great place...
Tasty, wholesome food. Good value for money. As a spot to go for a drink it is only OK. Good for occasions, like birthday and engagement parties.
Food is really good and tasty also reasonably priced. Evening dinner menu starts at 4. Portion sizes are very good
Great place for food and party

Good seating area outside. If your a Smoker or not? Pool table plenty Sports like Premier league Rugby GAA. On multiple TVs. Good atmosphere. Nice for Family. Staff very good. Gets very busy at 1pm for Dinners. Nice hot fresh food served daily. Comfy surrounding nice seating inside and outside. Great for that special occasion.
I have my lunch there regularly. You get what you ask for. Varied menu and very prompt and pleasant service. Have no hesitation recommending the arches for lunch.
It was simply a happy moments with friends to rejoice and celebrate

Absolutely enjoyed every moment. Arrived just prior to 9pm on a summer Tuesday. Still busy. Back at the Locke today and Sophie did an awesome job of taking care of our group. I told her I wanted one of the T-shirts and she went out of her way to find just the one I wanted.

Had a fantastic evening here for my sister's hen. The menu was perfect and we had a nice quiet area to ourselves. The staff was very accommodating and friendly. They catered for different dietary requirements and last minute requests with a smile! They made our job as organisers so much easier. Would highly recommend for a fun party night.

A great place to hang out. Friendly staff, good food, drinks, live music. You can choose to sit inside or outside (located along the city canal). I was lucky enough to visit this place when there were live music and Riverdance show. A very popular place in Limerick City.
Great place. Such a popular och welcoming place. Lot's of space, both indoor and outdoor. We got a proper Irish live band with a dancer performing in the middle of the pub

Great place to sit outside when the weather is nice. There are lots of tables outside and the inside is quite large. Last weekend, the weather was nice and there was rugby on so the place was hopping. It seems like a good spot for watching a match/meeting up with a group of friends.
Rapidly becoming my favorite bar in limerick. Either sitting outside on the patio or beside the river, it is a wonderful experience.
One of my favs in the city. Excellent ambience. Grt music and good collection of drinks. If you are going on weekends might wanna reach early, it gets crowded very fast. Very helpful staff.
Informative tour with kind people. Very passionate about their product and mission, and it is reflected in the best possible way as they give the brewery tour. Hope to be back soon.

The food here is great and decent prices too. Theres a lovely atmosphere in the evenings and its perfect for a pint. Its also in a great location and is nice to sit outside if the weather is clear. Friendly and helpful staff too.

For a pub it has a great location, close to the river, John's Castle and the city centre. High standard pub food and life music on occasion. Good place to sit outside as there is a large outdoor area. Good atmosphere and attentive staff.
Service was very nice, had a lovely girl who helped in anyway possible. The seafood platter can easily be split and eaten by 2. The food was great and the Irish music and dancing was amazing to see.
The seafood pie is delicious and the fish n chips was the best out of 5 places in Ireland so far. Great food and great service and the live music and entertainment is superb as well.

Great bar in the summer if you can get a seat outside and the weather is good! They have traditional Irish music and dancing every night for when the weather isn't as nice but probably my favourite pub in limerick. Great food too.

This place was a delightful surprise to find in Limerick. Their steak and fisherman's pie were done perfectly, combined with some delicious oysters. The star of the trip was definitely the Irish music and dancer they had. If you are traveling through Limerick it is a must.
Lovely outdoor seating by the river, my bf and I both had the fish n chips and we couldn't fault it beautiful. Place was packed on a Tues summer's evening, says it all
Good food and service. I visited for lunch. One of the things I liked is their menu, which is affordable. They even have a trio option. The staff is friendly. And I enjoyed the cheeseburger.
Nice place to meet your friends and go crazy.. I mean, not so crazy haha but you can enjoy the music, drinks, good drinks and a beautiful garden outside. I do recommend!
Love the Pucan! Great place to watch the game. Tasty food. Great atmosphere and with good live bands.
Good pub, good atmosphere. Good for a stag or a hen. Nothing too special except the outdoor area. Great for a game
Great local pub! The first one I've been to when I arrived to Galway and I sure love coming back.
We had the Irish stew and the bangers and mash. Both were outstanding. They had live music. It was a great venue. Would definitely go back
Fast and friendly service. Staff were lovely and the food was first class. My first time in Galway I will definitely be back.
Loved this place! Tasty food and great music. Lively atmosphere. Perfect pint.
Lovely clean pub and restaurant. Food was fabulous and staff were very helpful..
Good place for a night out in the center of Galway. Good variety of drinks. Beer garden pretty.
We are twice at this pub in Galway during a recent stay and really enjoyed both visits. Live music was an added plus. Loved the Lamb stew and my wife had excellent fish.
Great food, even the traditional Irish meal. Awesome music. Great place to eat and e joy traditional Irish music.
Really good food! ! Great deals on food too. And the staff are lovely
Very nice sports bar and event location. Food looked awesome, but we didn't try any. Great atmosphere and nice staff. Live music was cool as well. Very busy on weekends.
It is my favourite pub in Galway. The wings are great and the gin tonics have always very good deals. If you're visiting galway don't miss Pcn and its garden.

Great bar/restaurant located in the centre of Kilkenny town. Returning customer due to a recommendation from a work colleague. Went here again today and the food was absolutely top notch. The customer service honestly couldn't have being bettered either as the waiters were extremely attentive and knowledgeable of the menu. Would highly recommended this to anyone looking for a nice classy pub/sports bar and possibly interested in some really tasty food. This bar looks great as a sports bar and shows regular popular sports.
I love this place. The food is excellent and the staff are always outstanding, pleasant and so efficient. I would highly recommend.

On a recent trip to visit Kilkenny I was pleasantly surprised that Paris Texas has undergone extensive renovations! It had been years since I lived there so my memories of this place revolves around live music and good friends. It still has a familiarness but the new stuff makes it so much better!

Absolutely AMAZING food. One of the best pulled pork sandwiches I've ever had as well as the Lamb Clank. The live music can be heard throughout the entire venue which is just fantastic. Once you finish with your meal I HIGHLY recommend stopping by the Whiskey Bar to enjoy the music and company. Highly entertaining and interactive!

Just got back from the bar, wonderful experience! The music was lovely tonight full of folk songs and humour. The people were all very nice and the food was wonderful. I had the regular size chips and salsa as well as the steak tip fajita and it was enough for 3 people. The food and drinks were result available in good timing and the bar was full until around 8:30. I couldn't have imagine a better place to go in Kilkenny on an early night such a great cultural experience.
Super food, great ambiance. Cosy and casual great for few drinks too. Definitely recommend it to everyone to visit it at some stage.

The atmosphere is very welcoming and the staff were very polite. My work place had booked a table for us, it was well set up and ready when we arrived. I ordered the buffalo blue burger, it was beautifully cooked and delicious.
Wow. Came highly recommended and it didn't disappoint. Super tasty food in a gorgeous atmosphere.
The food was delicious (and decently priced), the atmosphere was great, the bartender service was amazing, the hygiene levels were good.... Clearly an amazing pub. Really recommend going there!

A lovely bar and restaurant. If you're a whiskey drinker you'll love this place. Huge selection with a huge range of prices. Also I'm a big chicken wing eater. And this place has great wings. So if you like good food or a good drink go here. I'd highly recommend it. The staff are all so helpful and pleasant. Had a great night here. Will definitely return next time I visit Kilkenny
Food was lovely but the portions were massive! Don't order too much as you probably won't be able to finish it. Nice friendly staff and atmosphere. Loved the decor.
Had a very tasty blue cheese burger. Location is quite big. Due to a misunderstanding we got one extra dessert, which was nice.
Food was amazing and price was very reasonable and great live music
Great spot for diner and drinks. I had the Lamb sirloin. it was cooked perfectly and was accompanied by fresh vegetables. Also had the stuffed mushrooms to start which were very nice.

Always very good food and welcoming staff. Even tho you can see they are very busy and dealing with difficult client. But always very friendly and a menu to cater to anyone. Chicken wings are a local delicacy.
Great pub for beer and atmosphere! Always a great buzz. Nice local pub with good selection of beer wine and cocktails. They also serve coffee and a small food menu.
A friendly efficient, good humoured staff..I really enjoy every visit!
Cool people, great range of drinks and...love their Spritz on sunny days
Great place great vib to relax Sunday morning for coffee watch the world go by
Nice place. Always busy at the centre of city. Nicely decorated to have small party arrangements

Nice spot to watch the city go by. They have beers and spirits, tea and coffee. Good place for a hot whiskey! Limited food (basics like scones, toasties etc). Definitely check out the improv group that do a weekly show upstairs, it's only 5 for a fun night out
What a bar. Superb staff including Sonya,Mary,Brendan and Ian. The clientele form the most eclectic and iconoclastic people you could ever hope to meet. And you'll never guess...table service.
One of the most epic bars in Cork city. Sometimes they have life music. Good environment.
Well...all can I say is 5 stars...price is ok , nice friendly staff, they gave a slice of pizza for everybody in the pub. Well done..
Great spot. Lovely selection of beers and an excellent record shop located above it. I'd always try and drop in when visiting Cork.
One of the top places in Cork to have a drink, chat or enjoy music!(check the plugd vinyl store)
Always love coming here for a few drinks. It has a warm friendly atmosphere and great selection of drink on tap

Great spot for a night out. Great atmosphere and the staff are sound. Music downstairs is great and there's a club upstairs that has bands and Djs. Drinks aren't too expensive and service is very fast. Would definitely recommend it for a few pints on your night out.
Lovely pub in the city centre, very good for coffee in the morning, great place to go for a drink in the night time.

Really nice bar with a great selections of beers and wines. They also have a good selection of teas & coffees with some nice local cakes during the day. Really friendly staff too. It gets very busy most of the time so get there early if you want a seat!

A great little pub that's in something of a time warp. Original decor, no TV and no loud music. There's a fridge behind the bar with a selection of craft beers. Lots of character and a great spot for a sociable pint. The toilets are also in a time warp tho!

For generations Callanan's has been a quality authentic bar hidden away in the heart of the city. It has something for everyone, somehow happily mixing older locals with a younger modern crowd. It's a decent bar for everyone. There's also a traditional Cork 'Rings' board, but it may but be available on weekends when it's busy.
Hard to give it 5 stars as there wont be room for me anymore. Cracking boozer though. Long live Callanans.
Great bar. Unassuming in looks from outside. A hidden gem
One of a frightening few quintessential irish pubs, love it

Best pint of stout to be had anywhere. I always love coming back here when I visit Cork. Lived in Cork for 3 years. This pub is like time travelling 50 years. The Beamish is perfect everytime. The staff are sound, the atmosphere is chilled, the prices very fair. Great for a pint and chat with mates. Don't ever change
A classic old world cork city bar. Undoubtedly some of the best stout available anywhere. Good value and few frills.

...we went in last night feeling very beamish indeed and had a pint of Murphy`s there after....both on draught and excellent... can`t really say which one was nicer... extra bonus, power-cut, so the candles came out... lovely atmosphere... thanks guys for that time-warp-feeling... we shall meet again next time I`m in Cork... can`t wait
Good for a few pints of creamy Beamish or a bottle of local craft beer. Rob and Reg behind the bar are both sound. The background music is always good too.
Traditional pub, friendly ambiance, great environment, delicious beer.
Great trad musicians there last night. Great atmosphere for a small pub.
Great Beamish, small pub so nice to get a seat.
A country pub smack in the middle of the city - was disappointed with zero Guinness taps but my god the Murphy's in there is the best you'll ever have! Great little find!
Friendly staff. Friendly crowd. Great whiskey selection. Great Bemish. A real traditional Irish pub. You could be in any village or town in Cork when you step in there. Cash only
Brilliant traditional pub in the heart of cork. Always a great atmosphere. (Get in early because its small & it packs up real quick!). Great pint too. ;)
Absolutely Amazing place to visit. Every person who served us was exceptional. Highly recommend.
One of the most iconic pubs in Cork. Many a happy pint I've had there over the years. Awesome staff and wonderful atmosphere...

Centre of Cork city only bar on Patrick's Street cork. Nice place to come sit with friends or on your own. Tight fit but very manageable not great for push chairs or Maybe even Wheel chairs narrow but wheelchair access from the front door as ramp here. Toilets upstairs bit of a climb but fine bar could watch Sport here. Drinks a bit on the High side. Get spot to sit and just chill out.
Great outdoir seating and atmosphere.very attentive staff and owner.
First stop on walking tour, had the best Irish Coffee ever! The owner said the recipe was a secret
Lovely old bar they do great irish coffee
Beautiful pub. Lovely staff. Great range of drinks. Really cosy and right in the centre of the City
Lovely old fashion pub. Comfortable not noisy.
Lovely pub Quiet at the moment and very relaxing. Some French speaking visitors in early May.
Lovely, friendly place. Good pub food.
Prime location on Patricks street. Nice for a sunny day. Some drinks a little overpriced but nice pub and location in general.
Lovely welcoming pub with great atmosphere. Plus gorgeous Irish coffee
nice bar. would easily walk past this but lovely for a pit stop drink
Famously good. Amazing Irish coffee and no better place to sit and people watch in fine weather

A well known Cork establishment located in the middle of it's main shopping street. A very pleasant place to take a break from shopping. They have a wide choice of beers and bar food here is excellent
Food is grand and kids eat free. Very reasonable price and staff are friendly. Menu includes gluten free options
Nice atmosphere and high standard of interior. The best place to go with friend visiting Ireland for a few days.
Nice pub, I've only been there for the full Irish breakfasts, haven't had a pint yet, but it looks like a nice spot. Decent clean, and a nice sized smoking area out back. Massive car park too.
Gerry malone senior drinks there ,, be worthy
Awesome pub. It has a protected from the elements smoking place.
Food and service good. Comfortable and cosy.
Love the soup and sambos .And the lovely blonde lady who serves us our food
Real good grub and pints.
Nice enough tbh god bless
Excellent food and friendly service.
Very nice food and staff very friendly
Great breakfast an excellent service
Nice food never fails would highly recommend
Very nice pub and staff. Music on the night was excellent, shame there wasn't a bigger crowd to hear him.
The food was greAt and the lady that give us are food is a great place to go for sunday dinner
Great bar very friendly staff highly recommend a visit
Great venue for party, staff so friendly and very helpful
Great spot beer, banter, pool, darts
Nice pub, cheap drinks and always has live sports
Excellent local pub to have a few pints and hav a craic
Great bar for sports and if you are interested in darts, pool,or poker
Great pool tables. Friendly and accommodating staff. A real Cork pub.
The owner is a nice and helpful publican
The bar maid Michelle is a gem. She entertains and runs the bar at its best.
