Would definately recommend this place for a night out.
Nice beer and food. Bingo is enjoyable on the Tuesday night although it's hard to navigate the number of stairs after afew beers!
Big, fancy, and sprawling. 3 words I'd use to describe this place. It may be too big though as a lot of space seems to be unused.
LOVELY warm atmosphere helpful staff lovely food..and of course Drinks.
Great atmosphere when rugby on TV. Staff always in great humour and service top class.

Staff is wonderful and brilliant, always simling. The building is just amazing, take few minutes to walk around and admire the woodwork and the antiques - just amazing. Food is finger licking good and prices are more than fair. Highly recommend it, is worth each single penny.
Various nights of live music, pub quizzes and fun nights. Lots of food options, and so many different spots to sit, whether it's in the action or a cosy corner.
Just went in for a drink and I really enjoyed it. The pint of Murphy's was lovely, service was good and the atmosphere was just like a traditional Irish pub.
Great place to drink the staff are top class and plenty of sport to watch on the various screens , I would recommend it lively pub at week ends.
Staff friendly, nice place for a drink. Open fire and outdoor area
Very good sport's bar 4 screens. Good sporting atmosphere.
Cool pub to watch the match. Only place I found in Kinsale that we could watch rugby.
Good for a pint in the afternoon if there's football on.
If your looking for a great townie pub this is it
Sports bar. Is what it is.
A great sports bar watched Liverpool thump Arsenal 4-0 which made it even better. Would deffo recommend this bar.
What a great night! Thank you so much! A better pint of guinness youll find hard to find! A great nights craic! See yous again soon!
Beautiful place. Excellent and friendly service. If 8 ever come back to Cork, this will be the first place to go. Thanks for everything
Great pint just like it was during the sixties
Corkonian legend Joe Mac plays every Sunday, anything else?
Wonderful experience with friendly staff and Jer the proprietor. I' ll be back.

Good place, lovely waiters, it's a amazing place to have a drink and maybe eat something, every now and then there is traditional live irish music, so for those who enjoy a bit of culture, it's worth a look.
Always a great favourite of mine,nice friendly,cosy pub in the heart of the city.Rather expensive for drink but probably worth it for entertainment.
Brilliant pub great sandwiches and really helpful nice staff couldn't find better

A little slice of honest cork! Join the locals for an amazing toastie, check out the walls for some history, or just sit and chill for a quite pint and gather your thoughts.....to say the staff are friendly is a little like saying the Beatles were just a band.
Great staff and very friendly atmosphere,lovely food very clean and tidy
Great sandwiches nice pints in a traditional pub from the 19th century.
Buy a drink, roll the dice, guess odd or even, win another drink or drinks to the same value... Only on Wednesday nights but we'll worth trying.. Nice smoking area, heated. Nice relaxed atmosphere
This is somewhere you end up after a big night out and just let lose and go for a dance. It's a little bit busy but the atmosphere was great

Great place to meet friends or colleagues for a nite out. They have a wide selection of beer and cocktails to choose from at the bar. It is wheelchair accessible and friendly. There are wheelchair accessible restrooms.
what a great place to relax #cocktails were of right mixture and staff friendly
One of the best spots in cork. Everyone should go at least once

One of my favourite venues in Cork to have a catch up with pals. The music is always to my liking and the staff are very friendly! Service has always been good, even on very busy evenings the staff still manage quite well to give everyone a chance to place their orders. The quizzes and 'minigames' they host just add to the reasons to come here!
Great place for a drink. Sunday nights are unreal there. Great place to hang out.

First there was the Brg, then it became like a supersized Brg. This was with the amalgamation of it with the Crannrg and the Hairy Lemon. In more recent years its downsized slightly again. But it has always remained an amazing place to be. Between the fun, music and the drink, the Brg is a venue that has entertained generations and hopefully will keep doing so.
Outstanding pub. First choice for a lively night out at a late bar in Cork. Great music, really great staff. They always have some kind of deal or activity going on, which is good fun. Top spot
Alternative place, great music, a lot of games during the week "beer prizes"
Great bar. Seems quite popular. Fabulous outside area. Finger food is great and easy to set up tabs for multiple parties.
The company and the weather made it a fantastic place to be.
Love this pub. Lovely beer garden. Relatively fast service, even at the height of st patricks day. Would highly recommend
It is the place to be when there is a match. And if you like crowds. Huge garden, lots of space inside.
By far the best beer garden in Cork. Had the best day soaking up a bit of Ireland Summer Sun!
Nice place, refreshing pints and amazing people!
Fantastic outdoor beer garden with a huge TV screen, perfect for watching the match.
Tasty cocktails. Great atmosphere. What more could you want!
Cozy place to meet up with friends and colleagues.
Good place, the cabins there for the matches were very good.
Fantastic bar friendliest staff you could meet great atmosphere

This a great place, great staff and maybe the best place for quite atmosphere or to watch a match. Grand place to have drink and here you will have wide choice of branded liquid, gin or pint. I will come back.
One of very few bars close to the city with real public house service. I highly recommend a visit.
Good service, friendly people, nice atmosphere, clean restrooms, ordered pizza from a nearby restaurant and enjoyed a good night with friends.
Great place anytime of the year. The staff are kind curious and most accommodating. The crossword is a lovely touch.
Good bar. Nice crowd. Good beer garden. Good smoking area.
Great bar for watching rugby, great selection of beer and wine, nicely decorated bar.

This newer bar replacing The Gateway is considered one of the oldest pubs in the city, and apparently the Duke of Wellington and the Earl of Ormond once stopped in here with their horses for a gatt back in the day. (Probably a Beamish!)
Really great little spot with a lot of history. minutes from everything and great during the week.

Great little pub at the end of barracks Street. Was only here once on the Jazz weekend and it was brilliant. Was an incredible band called the jazzmasters or something who were absolutely class. The vibe and atmosphere in the bar was cool. We only stayed around 2hrs here but will be a place I'll be sure to stop off at anytime I'm in town.
Fantastic food and service for a reasonble price. Steaks are particularly good!
Love Soos. Great selection of authentic street food dishes. Always delicious.
Nice place to drink. Great place to have a dance,  security are grand at the door,  clean place.
Always a great night here, good cocktails.
Very good food and friendly staff. Can't find words for the sundaes.
We realy enjoyed been in Soho .The food was delicious .The atmosphere was very good.I really recommend Soho..Fantastic place.
Classic American burger was huge, delicious. Came with proper chips, stuffed.
Brilliant customer service from the staff. The food was delicious and the cocktails we equally incredible. Great place for a date night or a night out.
Lively, great music. Friendly atmosphere with a good mix of ages.
Food was nice,lovy place to catch up with family and have a bite to eat.great at.osphere for a night out.

Nice pub. Looks small but stretches far back. Nice pint of Guinness. Good range of drinks on offer. Great atmosphere. Serves cocktail sausages and Black pudding after matches. Good place for groups. Large beer garden overlooking the River Shannon.
Nice pub to chill out. And they have the best guinness in town.
Love this pub! One of the best spots in Limerick for a post rugby match pint!
If you didn't know, this is the oldest pub in Limerick! Quaint little place that pours one of the best pints of Guinness in town.
Great pub for great company and best pint in limerick. Also the owners are lovely people.
Great spot. Lovely old world traditional pub inside, with a lovely beer garden overlooking the Shannon out the back.
Great atmosphere, really welcoming and nice staff. A fantastic pint. Great view of the river from the outside area. A must see when visiting Limerick.
Great pub with superb views of the castle from the back courtyard. Try to go here after a Munster match for an incredible time.
Lovely old pub on the river Shannon, popular with young and old. Always great atmosphere after matches in nearby Thomond Park.
Typical Irish pub. Attendant was polite and the price is fine. There's a space just by the river which must be awesome in a sunny day.
Very interesting layout, with comfortable booths. love the set up for bands. Saw Woody and friends perform, such fun! Good beer selection and multiple bars so minimal queuing required.
Could spend the whole day just looking at all the different bottles of beers ales etc etc on the walls. Lovely food and even better atmosphere. Definitely next time will be going back there again.

A few friends and I went to Porterhouse for drinks like every other tourist in Dublin, and overall, despite everyone here basically being a tourist, it was enjoyable and the bar is huge. This is basically a four level bar, so even when the bar is packed with people, there is a lot of space.

Loved it. Enjoying a good meal while listening to great live Irish music. Friendly, good and fast service, as well, what more could you ask for. As we enjoyed it so much, we went there 2 days in a row.

Delicious food and a fun atmosphere can be had at Porterhouse Temple Bar. We ate her on our first night in Ireland, and again on our last night two weeks later. Weave your way through all the floors of the bar and head all the way up to the top floor for the restaurant. The food here is tasty and delicious, and they have the most amazing beer battered onion rings ever! Eat here... it's wonderful!

Large selection of their own beers and guest beers, including a ginormous bottle list. Mixed drinks and wine also served. Their food is excellent. The Beef & Porter Stew, steak sandwich, and salmon were all delicious.
Awesome food, friendly staff and a fantastic atmosphere including live Irish music. Would definitely be a place to bring any foreign friends visiting Dublin.

Fantastic bar! Huge amount of atmosphere, live music. Really enjoyed the whole experience, so much so we returned. They have their own brewery with their products on tap. Their local porter is very tasty!
Great music, great atmosphere and really good vibe. They had some live music when we went out and that just added to the vibe. They have a good range of beers. Worth checking out.
Great selection of beers. House beers are pretty good. Lots of space with tables in corners for a small pub vibe. Can recommend the onion rings.
What a brilliant place. ALL about the music and atmosphere!

One of the best kept secrets in town. Tiny little cozy pub with amazing local musicians. If youre looking for a friendly, quaint and rustic little pub this is the place. Youll remember your visit forever.
Best little pub in Ireland as in clonakilty west cork
Takes you back in time
A magical night, you can't describe. The Guinness tastes better with your music.
One not to miss if you're ever in Clonakilty!
Authentic bar with beautiful traditional Irish music.
Nice friendly pub
Lovely space.
A little gem!

I've been to a few gay bars in Ireland, and I was expecting a dingy pub-like bar. Chambers is a nice bar with modern decor. My colleague and I met several people throughout the night; everyone was very friendly. I look forward to coming back!
Popped in during Corkfest for a minute as "Cassette" was playing. We loved the band and the bar was filled with people having fun. Wish I'd stayed longer actually.

We came across this bar as it seemed to be the only place in close proximity that was open and hoppin at 2-2:30am. We went in for a few drinks and some dancing. Definitely a good place when you want to stay out and keep the party going.
I never go to Cork without going for a night out in Chambers! Great atmosphere, great music, great staff and never a dull moment. Looking for the Craic, you found it!
Always great music, staff and crowd.
Very young crowd on a Wednesday night but all dancing and having fun to some 90s tunes.
Nice gay pub with live music. Must visit
Fun gay bar, sounds like there isn't usually a line. Nice big dance floor.
Great spot and amazing cocktails!
Best night club ever

Just stopped off for dinner on the way home back to County Down amazing bit of food steak is always outstanding and so was the fish Ive had. Thanks for the great custom and great food and hospitality.
Brilliant food and service. Cosy atmosphere.
Great buzz, good coffee and food.
Foods amazing and staff really friendly. Definitely be back next time in Dundalk.

Great food, great service & a pleasure to be in, I went to McGeoughs this evening with family and was very impressed with the friendliness of all the staff members, the relaxed atmosphere and the tasty dishes. Definitely will be back again!
Great food. Staff so friendly. Highly recommend. Best Brunch.
Had a wonderful meal here, chicken wings were to die for (you could lick the bowl clean) steak cooked to perfection, great service, friendly staff. Will be back again.
Fantastic meal last night with family. Top service from friendly staff and food excellent. Place buzzing with people. Always a great place for great food!

Went there on Sunday evening, mothers day. Service bang on, food gorgeous. Am a fairly regular customer but I tried beef +Guinness pie for a change. It was melt in the mouth gorgeous, piping hot and service quick considering how busy it was. A lovely end to mothers day, thank's guys.
Excellent staff,fast,efficient,courteous and attentive.Good selection on their menu and the food was excellent.
